honeywell.printer.configuration.expcl

Class GeneralStatus_ExPCL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.expcl.PrinterData_ExPCL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.expcl.PrinterState_ExPCL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.expcl.GeneralStatus_ExPCL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class GeneralStatus_ExPCL
extends PrinterState_ExPCL
    This class handles the data from an <ESC>S query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    EPrinter Error
    LHead Lever Latched
    PPaper Present
    BBattery Status
    HHead Temperature Acceptable
    SText Queue Status
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • GeneralStatus_ExPCL

        public GeneralStatus_ExPCL(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_ExPCL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

        public boolean getPrinterError_IsPresent()
        Indicates if getPrinterError() parameter is present.

        This function is useful to determine if the given parameter is supported on the current printer. Because of differences in configuration, hardware or version certain parameter may not exist and the results returned by the parameter getPrinterError() may not be valid.

        Returns:
        If the parameter is present and valid true, false otherwise.
